-------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODIFICATION FUNCTIONS

I modified the original code in order to it can be executed with octave.
Octave is similar to matlab but free. It can be download at
 
   http://www.octave.org
 
This version must be executed with octave and the command line 
must be:
 
> octave --traditional

-----------------------------------------------------------
SOME FUNCTIONS OBTAINED FROM:
Original address, http://www.ee.vt.edu/valenti/home.html
New address,      http://www.csee.wvu.edu/~mvalenti/

 * bin_state , utility to convert from integer to vector of bits.
 * bit_encode , encode a single bit.
 * check_matrix , finds the parity check matrix from the generator matrix.
 * cyclic_encode , encode an entire block of data.
 * cyclic_matrix , find the generator matrix of a block code.
 * syst_matrix , puts a generator matrix in systematic form.
 * int_state , utility to convert from vector of bits to integer.
 * interleave , utility that performs a block interleaving process.
 * mult_mod2 , muliplies a vector by a matrix modulo-2.
 * viterbi , the soft-decision Viterbi decoding algorithm.
 * shift_reg.m , maximum sequence register generator

